Happy 50th Birthday Y100!!!

As someone who grew up a fan of this radio station listening everyday it is a dream come true to work here. 

As a kid I remember listening to Kenny and Footy on the way to school then of course Elvis Duran who quickly became one of my idols in the radio biz (still crazy to think that I can call him a coworker and friend) I also have fond memories of Michael Yo on air as I came home from soccer practice when he was doing the very same show I’m doing right now! 

I can also remember hearing my favorite band Marion 5 for the first time ever on Y100 and even winning tickets to see them with a text contest I heard on air. Now anytime I giveaway tickets to someone I always think about the joy I felt winning my tickets as a teenager.

Never in a million years did I think I’d end up here and quite honestly the highlight of my career thus far has been getting the call to join the Y team. 

Over the last few years that I’ve been here I’ve dedicated so much time and energy to this brand in the hopes that other kids like me also grow up having fond memories of Y100. 

So if you’ve ever been a student on YHigh, an attendee to one of our many events including Jingle Ball, or you just enjoyed the content we’ve created on air and online I thank you from the bottom of my heart 💙 It is truly an honor to be a part of a legendary station like this and I can’t wait to see what Y100 is like in another 50 years!
Tia & Tio 💕
